<%#
  Add Funds hub — the "more ways to add funds" rail picker reached by swap()
  from the Get Entry Tokens picker (modals/auth/_tokens + _paypal_tokens).
  One modal id ('onramp-hub'); no internal step machine.

  Rails, in order: Coinbase (wired to the cdp-ramp buy preflight), PayPal
  (placeholder), Venmo (placeholder), Stripe single token (wired back to the
  Get Entry Tokens picker, which IS the Stripe checkout flow).

  Per-rail visibility is gated by onramp_rail_visible? (app/helpers/
  onramp_helper.rb): every rail shows locally, each gates on its own backend
  flag in production.

  FLAG-AWARE degrade (tokenFallback): the Coinbase rail buys USDC, which a web2
  kill-switch viewer (ENABLE_WEB2_USDC_ENTRY off) can NOT spend on an entry, so
  it is additionally hidden for that audience client-side. Without this, a quiet
  "More ways to add funds" hop from the (already-degraded) wallet-topup modal,
  or from the tokens picker, would put a flag-off web2 user one click from a
  real-money USDC buy that dead-ends their entry. tokenFallback mirrors the
  wallet-topup getter exactly (web2 mode AND the flag off, read from
  $store.session); web3 + flag-on web2 still see Coinbase. The Stripe entry-token
  rail stays visible for the degraded audience, so the hub never empties.

  Back-navigation returns to wherever the hub was opened FROM, keyed on the
  props it was opened with:
    - props.returnModal === 'wallet-topup'  -> Back swaps to wallet-topup
      (opened from the Coinbase-forward Top Up Wallet modal).
    - otherwise (the tokens-picker path)    -> Back swaps to auth at
      props.returnStep || 'tokens-picker' (the existing _tokens /
      _paypal_tokens "More ways to add funds" link, unchanged).

  Modeled on modals/_wallet_deposit + modals/_cdp_ramp. CRITICAL: rendered
  inside a host template x-if, so a SINGLE root element. x-data exposes props
  the same way _wallet_deposit does; single-quote everything inside the
  double-quoted x-data / @click attributes.
%>
<div x-data="{
       get props() { return ($store.modals.current() || {}).props || {} },
       get tokenFallback() { return $store.session.mode === 'web2' && !$store.session.web2UsdcEntry }
     }"
     class="relative">

  <%# Top-right close. Backdrop close still works too. %>
  <button @click="$store.modals.close()"
          class="absolute top-0 right-0 -mt-2 -mr-2 text-secondary hover:text-heading text-xl leading-none z-10"
          aria-label="Close">&times;</button>

  <div class="text-center pt-1 mb-3">
    <h3 class="text-heading font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Add Funds</h3>
  </div>
  <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-4 text-center">
    Pick how you'd like to fund your entry. More options are on the way.
  </p>

  <div class="space-y-3">
    <% if onramp_rail_visible?(:coinbase) %>
      <%# Coinbase — wired to the existing cdp-ramp buy preflight, the same
          handoff the /wallet Buy USDC button and the wallet-deposit modal
          use. swap() (not open) because we are already inside the host.

          Gated behind !tokenFallback (single root inside the template, the
          x-if rule): a web2 kill-switch viewer can not fund an entry with USDC,
          so this USDC-buy rail must not be a dead-end for them. See the header
          note. web3 + flag-on web2 always see it. %>
      <template x-if="!tokenFallback">
        <button type="button" data-onramp-rail="coinbase"
                @click="$store.modals.swap('cdp-ramp', { flow: 'buy', step: 'preflight' })"
                class="w-full flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border border-strong hover:border-primary bg-inset transition text-left">
          <span class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-white font-extrabold text-lg" style="background-color:#0052FF">C</span>
          <span class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <span class="block text-heading font-semibold text-sm">Coinbase</span>
            <span class="block text-xs text-secondary">Buy USDC with a card or bank</span>
          </span>
          <svg class="shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-muted" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.25 4.5l7.5 7.5-7.5 7.5"/>
          </svg>
        </button>
      </template>
    <% end %>

    <% if onramp_rail_visible?(:coinflow) %>
      <%# Coinflow — wired to the buy-1-entry hosted-checkout flow. Clones the
          Coinbase rail card, but is NOT gated behind !tokenFallback: unlike the
          Coinbase USDC buy, Coinflow mints a spendable ENTRY TOKEN directly, so
          it's useful to the web2 kill-switch audience too (like the Stripe
          token rail). tmCoinflowBuyOne() POSTs /tokens/coinflow_order then
          redirects to Coinflow's hosted checkout. %>
      <button type="button" data-onramp-rail="coinflow"
              @click="tmCoinflowBuyOne('single')"
              class="w-full flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border border-strong hover:border-primary bg-inset transition text-left">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-white font-extrabold text-lg" style="background-color:#14B8A6">CF</span>
        <span class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <span class="block text-heading font-semibold text-sm">Coinflow &middot; $19</span>
          <span class="block text-xs text-secondary">Buy 1 entry token with a card</span>
        </span>
        <svg class="shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-muted" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.25 4.5l7.5 7.5-7.5 7.5"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    <% end %>

    <% if onramp_rail_visible?(:paypal) %>
      <%# PayPal — placeholder. Visually complete, non-interactive, tagged
          "Soon". Wire it to the paypal_tokens flow when the rail goes live. %>
      <div data-onramp-rail="paypal"
           class="w-full flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border border-subtle bg-inset opacity-60">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-white font-extrabold text-lg" style="background-color:#003087">P</span>
        <span class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <span class="block text-heading font-semibold text-sm">PayPal</span>
          <span class="block text-xs text-secondary">Pay with your PayPal balance</span>
        </span>
        <span class="shrink-0 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest font-bold text-muted bg-surface border border-subtle rounded-full px-2 py-0.5">Soon</span>
      </div>
    <% end %>

    <% if onramp_rail_visible?(:venmo) %>
      <%# Venmo — placeholder, same treatment as PayPal (shares the PayPal
          backend rail once live). %>
      <div data-onramp-rail="venmo"
           class="w-full flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border border-subtle bg-inset opacity-60">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-white font-extrabold text-lg" style="background-color:#008CFF">V</span>
        <span class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <span class="block text-heading font-semibold text-sm">Venmo</span>
          <span class="block text-xs text-secondary">Pay from your Venmo balance</span>
        </span>
        <span class="shrink-0 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest font-bold text-muted bg-surface border border-subtle rounded-full px-2 py-0.5">Soon</span>
      </div>
    <% end %>

    <% if onramp_rail_visible?(:stripe) %>
      <%# Stripe single token — wired back to the Get Entry Tokens picker,
          which IS the Stripe checkout flow. Mirrors the board showTokensPanel
          props so the picker mounts clean. %>
      <button type="button" data-onramp-rail="stripe"
              @click="$store.modals.swap('auth', { step: 'tokens-picker', mintedCount: 0, mintedBalance: 0, errorText: '', redirectUrl: '', txSignature: '' })"
              class="w-full flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border border-strong hover:border-primary bg-inset transition text-left">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-white font-extrabold text-lg" style="background-color:#635BFF">S</span>
        <span class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <span class="block text-heading font-semibold text-sm">Card &middot; $19</span>
          <span class="block text-xs text-secondary">Buy one entry token with a card</span>
        </span>
        <svg class="shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-muted" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.25 4.5l7.5 7.5-7.5 7.5"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <%# Back to wherever the hub was opened from. returnModal === 'wallet-topup'
      slides back to the Top Up Wallet modal; otherwise back to the entry-tokens
      picker at props.returnStep (defaulting to the picker), the unchanged
      _tokens / _paypal_tokens path. Single expression keyed on returnModal. %>
  <button type="button"
          @click="props.returnModal === 'wallet-topup' ? $store.modals.swap('wallet-topup', {}) : $store.modals.swap('auth', { step: (props.returnStep || 'tokens-picker') })"
          class="block mx-auto mt-4 text-sm text-secondary hover:text-heading transition">
    &larr; Back
  </button>

  <%# Defines window.tmCoinflowBuyOne for the Coinflow rail above. Inside the
      single root div so the hub stays a single element under its x-if host. %>
  <% if onramp_rail_visible?(:coinflow) %><%= render "tokens/coinflow_script" %><% end %>
</div>
